    Upper Gastrointestinal Endoscopy in Subjects with Positive Faecal Occult Blood Test Undergoing Colonoscopy: Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis.
In FOBT+ subjects there is an appreciable prevalence of UGI cancers and other CSL. Anaemia but not symptoms or colonic pathology are linked to UGI lesions. While the data suggest that same day gastroscopy in FOBT+ subjects undergoing colonoscopy yields approximately 25% more malignancies as colonoscopy alone, prospective data are required to determine the cost-efficacy of dual-endoscopy as a standard of care for al FOBT+ subjects.
