TrkB overexpression inhibited the activation of TGF-ß/SMAD signaling and alleviated hepatic fibrosis both in vitro and in vivo. These findings speculate that TrkB could be a significant suppressor of hepatic fibrosis and confers a potential therapeutic target in hepatic fibrosis.
